Compass CSS (http://wiki.github.com/chriseppstein/compass)
Depends on SASS (http://sass-lang.com)

To install required software for development:
  * install Ruby
  * install RubyGems: sudo apt-get install rubygems
    + on Ubuntu (if gems are not added to path): edit .bashrc to include:
      export PATH=/var/lib/gems/1.8/bin:$PATH
  * install SASS:
    * sudo gem install haml
  * install Compass:
    * gem sources --add http://gems.github.com/
    * sudo gem install chriseppstein-compass

To modify css files:
  * run "compass -w" from this directory
  * edit src .sass files, they will be auto-compiled/copied
    when you save changes.

Default location of .sass libraries:
  * /var/lib/gems/1.8/gems/compass-0.10.2

Syntax coloring for Aptana (and eclipse?)
  * http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1474096/using-haml-sass-with-eclipse
